#http://www.epicurious.com/recipes/food/views/Broccoli-Soup-with-Leeks-and-Thyme-363691
IN	3 tablespoons butter
IN	3 cups chopped leeks (white and pale green parts only; about 3 large)
IN	6 teaspoons chopped fresh thyme, divided
IN	1 1/4 pounds broccoli crowns, chopped (about 8 generous cups)
IN	4 cups (or more) low-salt chicken broth
PR	Melt butter in large pot over medium-high heat. Add leeks and 4 teaspoons thyme; saut√© until leeks are almost soft, reducing heat if needed to prevent rapid browning, 7 to 8 minutes. Transfer 1/2 cup leeks to small bowl; reserve. Add broccoli and 4 cups broth to pot; bring to boil. Cover; boil until vegetables are tender, 8 to 10 minutes.
PR	Puree soup in blender until smooth. thin soup with more broth, if desired. Season with salt and pepper. Ladle into bowls; sprinkle with 2 teaspoons chopped thyme and reserved leeks.
